Arathane became Queen of Akan没l in [[1469 DR]], after succeeding her mother, the late Queen Cyndra.

In 1479 DR, [[Aoth Fezim]] of the [[Brotherhood of the Griffon]] sought out Queen Arathane to convince her to not give her support to [[Tchazzar]] in the invasion of [[Tymanther]], however he was unable to convince Queen Arathane to not attack the [[dragonborn]]. She changed her opinion later, when Aoth and members of the Firestorm Cabal killed the [[Fang dragon|gray]] [[dragon]] [[Vairshekellabex]].

That same year, she indirectly aided the [[deva]] [[Demascus]] to deal with [[Murmur]] and the cult of the [[Tharizdun|Elder Elemental Eye]] in Airspur.{{Cite digital book/Sword of the Gods}} In [[Marpenoth|Leafall]] of 1479 DR, Queen Arathane asked Demascus and [[Riltana]] to investigate potential trouble at an [[arambarium]] mine on [[Ithimir Isle]] off the coast of Akan没l.{{Cite digital book/Spinner of Lies|518}} She later went to Ithimir Isle alongside Demasccus, Riltana, [[Chant]] and [[Jaul Morven]] and fought [[Chenraya Xorlarrin]] and her minions. Unfortunately, the drow were able to [[Transmutation|transmute]] the arambarium into a staff and escape. The group traveled back to Airspur and entered a [[portal]] to the [[Demonweb Pits]] in the catacombs just as Chenraya was completing a ritual to open a gate to Menzoberranzan.{{Cite digital book/Spinner of Lies|3549}}  Demascus interrupted the ritual and grabbed most of the arambarium staff from Chenraya as she entered the gate.{{Cite digital book/Spinner of Lies|3592}}
